Modification notice (2026-07-13):

The upstream project was reduced to a standalone Agent Skill named
"format-content". The modified workflow accepts only Markdown text or a
readable .md file, always uses the red-and-white theme, emits a validated
clean section fragment plus a copy-button preview, and never publishes to
WeChat. Non-Markdown normalization, theme selection, theme generation, and
all other themes were removed from this distribution.

The bundled validate_gzh_html.py and wrap_preview.py scripts were locally
hardened. The validator now requires one balanced top-level section fragment
while accepting standard HTML void elements, and the preview wrapper now
limits marker replacement and HTML-escapes the source title.

The installable Skill is packaged under format-content/ so installers retain
its supporting references, scripts, assets, and metadata. Repository-level
documentation, tests, LICENSE, and NOTICE remain at the repository root; exact
copies of LICENSE and NOTICE are also bundled inside the installable Skill.

